  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Friendly practice&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I went on two occasions for 24hr BP monitor, and found the same nurse helped me on both occasions. I was quite nervous and she was very helpful and friendly, explaining things and helping me to relax.
I was seen on both occasions before my allotted time, which was good, so didn't have to wait too long at all.
The only thing I would like to remark on is that I was never told that the timing between readings is longer during the night. When it didn't read within the 30 mins I thought something was wrong with the machine. I then looked on internet and found out the night timing is longer. That would have been very helpful as I can panic quickly with machines. Otherwise I have nothing but praise for the lovely nurse. Well done! &lt;/CommentText&gt;
